  "local_port": 52156,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you cook pork chops in the oven?",
  "response": "Cooking pork chops in the oven is a simple and delicious way to prepare them. Here's a basic method to get you started:\n\n### Ingredients:\n- 4 pork chops (bone-in or boneless)\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 teaspoon salt\n- 1 teaspoon black pepper\n- 1 teaspoon garlic powder\n- 1 teaspoon paprika (optional)\n- 1 teaspoon dried thyme or rosemary (optional)\n\n### Instructions:\n\n1. **Preheat the Oven:**\n   Preheat your oven to 375\u00b0F (190\u00b0C).\n\n2. **Season the Pork Chops:**\n   Pat the pork chops dry with paper towels. This helps the seasoning stick better. Rub each pork chop with olive oil on both sides. In a small bowl, mix together the salt, pepper, garlic powder, paprika, and dried herbs (if using). Sprinkle the seasoning mixture evenly over both sides of the pork chops.\n\n3. **Sear the Pork Chops (Optional):**\n   Heat a skillet over medium-high heat. Add a little oil if needed. Sear the pork chops for about 2-3 minutes on each side until they are nicely browned. This step is optional but adds extra flavor.\n\n4. **Bake the Pork Chops:**\n   Transfer the pork chops to a baking dish or leave them in the oven-safe skillet if you seared them. Place the dish in the preheated oven. Bake for about 20-25 minutes, or until the internal temperature of the pork chops reaches 145\u00b0F (63\u00b0C). Cooking time may vary depending on the thickness of the chops.\n\n5. **Rest the Pork Chops:**\n   Remove the pork chops from the oven and let them rest for 5 minutes before serving. This allows the juices to redistribute, making the meat more tender and flavorful.\n\n6. **Serve:**\n   Serve the pork chops with your favorite sides, such as roasted vegetables, mashed potatoes, or a fresh salad.\n\n### Tips:\n- **Thickness Matters:** Thicker pork chops may require a longer cooking time, while thinner chops will cook faster.\n- **Check Temperature:** Use a meat thermometer to ensure the pork chops reach the safe internal temperature of 145\u00b0F (63\u00b0C).\n- **Variations:** You can add a glaze or sauce to the pork chops before baking, such as a honey mustard glaze, barbecue sauce, or a simple garlic butter.\n\nEnjoy your delicious oven-baked pork chops!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
